@{PARD}
@{B}Aasimon, Scild, General Description:@{UB}@{PAR}

Scilds are inhabitants of the good-aligned upper outer planes; like other
aasimon, they are the servants of the powers that reside in those planes.@{PAR}

Scilds have several forms in which they appear, one for each race they deal
with; not surprisingly, their most common forms are that of humans, half-elves,
elves, and dwarves; in addition, scilds may appear as either male or female,
although the male form is more common. A scild is able to change from one form
to another whenever it wishes; when dealing with more than one race at a time,
scilds usually choose to appear in their human forms. Scilds always appear as
the most-beautiful example of the chosen race (@{ " protectors " LINK "ImpPro:Data/ExtMonsterData/Aasimon, Scild, Protector.long/main"} and @{" defenders " LINK "ImpPro:Data/ExtMonsterData/Aasimon, Scild, Defender.long/main"} have a
charisma of 18, while @{" guardians " LINK "ImpPro:Data/ExtMonsterData/Aasimon, Scild, Guardian.long/main"} have a charisma of 19.) Scilds have muscular
bodies, and their eyes appear to glow softly. Perhaps the feature that sets them
apart most from the race they choose to emulate, is their graceful wings that
extend from their backs. Scilds in the form of a human male, appear much the
same as a deva.@{PAR}

